verbose_text: MAITs (CD161 hi Valpha7.2 +), a population of T cells that has recently been shown to reside long term in the liver, also had higher levels of autophagy when compared with CD161 mid or CD161 - T cells in the blood or liver, with each of these subsets having higher LC3 levels in the liver than their circulating counterparts (XREF_FIG C).
